  "doc_id": "24440",
  "text": "Washington and Perros [CITATION_1] proposed a decomposition algorithm for the analysis of tandem optical networks, whereby the queueing network was decomposed into subsystems, each consisting of two adjacent nodes. Each subsystem was analyzed using a modification of Courtois' algorithm, and the subsytems were solved iteratively until the results of each subsystem converged. The proposed algorithm was shown to be an improvement over the link independence algorithm. However, it was limited to the case where the link between adjacent nodes consisted of a single wavelength with a small number of sub-rate streams.",
